HEADWORD: Phoca
<hw>Pho"ca</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧"k⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., a seal, fr. Gr. <grk>fw`kh</grk>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of seals. It includes the common harbor seal and allied
species. See <er>Seal</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phocacean</ent>⟦br⟧
